premise_source_doc_sentence: Worldwide , too little iodine in the diet is the most common cause of hypothyroidism .
In countries with enough iodine in the diet , the most common cause of hypothyroidism is the autoimmune condition Hashimoto 's thyroiditis .
An estimated one-third of the world 's population currently lives in areas of low dietary iodine levels , making iodine-deficiency the most common cause of hypothyroidism and endemic goiter .
It can cause a number of symptoms , such as poor ability to tolerate cold , a feeling of tiredness , constipation , depression , and weight gain .
